<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1436,439,826]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,392,439,465]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Material examined</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[412,486,439,465]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
Stn. 
<number box="[473,486,439,465]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" value="3.0">3</number>
</emphasis>
: 
<date box="[508,640,440,466]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" value="2008-01-04">01.04.2008</date>
—a few sterile stems, up to 
<quantity box="[999,1072,440,466]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
high, on concretions. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1352,1426,439,465]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
Stn. 
<number box="[1413,1426,439,465]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" value="7.0">7</number>
</emphasis>
: 
<date box="[151,283,480,506]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" value="2008-03-27">27.03.2008</date>
—a few sterile colonies, up to 
<quantity box="[650,719,480,506]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
high, with both 
<taxonomicName box="[918,1045,480,505]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Halopterididae" genus="Antennella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[918,1045,480,505]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Antennella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like and pinnate stems, on algae and concretions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1436,439,826]" box="[197,786,559,586]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,356,559,585]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<typeStatus box="[197,258,559,585]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Type</typeStatus>
locality
</emphasis>
. Capocesto, 
<collectingCountry box="[507,596,560,586]" name="Croatia" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Croatia</collectingCountry>
, Mediterranean.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1436,439,826]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,311,599,625]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Remarks</emphasis>
. Though sterile, this species is recognizable by the heteromerous segmentation of the stem, the presence of generally 
<number box="[416,431,640,666]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" value="2.0">2</number>
(rarely 
<number box="[529,544,640,666]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" value="3.0">3</number>
) nematothecae on cauline segments, and the occurence of 
<taxonomicName box="[1255,1382,640,665]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Halopterididae" genus="Antennella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1255,1382,640,665]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Antennella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like stems in some colonies, as for instance those observed in the material from Stn. 
<number box="[1092,1109,680,706]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" value="7.0">7</number>
. For a complete description of 
<taxonomicName box="[182,329,720,745]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Halopterididae" genus="Halopteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="diaphana">
<emphasis box="[182,329,720,745]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">H. diaphana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its synonymy, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert" box="[601,807,720,746]" pageId="41" pageNumber="52" refString="Schuchert, P. (1997) Review of the family Halopterididae. Zoologische Verhandelingen, Leiden, 309, 1 - 162." type="journal article" year="1997">
Schuchert (
<number box="[734,798,720,746]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" value="1997.0">1997</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
